-- China’s Lifan to Build Uruguay Auto Plant, Infobae Reports
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-02-18T18:15:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-18/china-s-lifan-to-build-uruguay-auto-plant-infobae-reports.html
Chinese automobile manufacturer
 Lifan Industry Group Co. (601777)  plans to build a $150 million
automobile plant in Uruguay, news website  Infobae  reported.  The plant, which will create 500 jobs within three years,
may export the Lifan 320 and 620 models to Brazil and other
members of the Mercosur trading bloc, Buenos Aires-based Infobae
said, citing Industry Minister Roberto Kreimerman.  China  is Uruguay’s second-largest trading partner after
Brazil, the website said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman in Rio de Janeiro at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  